17:15.512 --> 17:16.948
-MITCH, IT'S OKAY.

17:21.387 --> 17:23.041
OKAY, I GOT YOU, OKAY.

17:29.483 --> 17:32.921
-WHERE?
-[GRUNTING] MY STOMACH.

17:34.401 --> 17:36.055
-BIG TIME SPASMS.
-OKAY.

17:37.491 --> 17:39.275
WINDJET ONE TO
HEADQUARTERS, COME IN.

17:40.102 --> 17:41.886
-DISPATCH:
WE READ YOU, WINDJET ONE.

17:42.017 --> 17:43.888
C.J. AND I ARE WITH MITCH, HE
HAS SEVER ABDOMINAL CRAMPING.

17:44.019 --> 17:47.066
HAVE AN AMBULANCE
AT THE MARINA AND NOTIFY ER.

17:47.762 --> 17:48.676
-DISPATCH:
COPY THAT, WINDJET ONE.

17:48.806 --> 17:49.764
-THANKS.

17:51.157 --> 17:53.507
-DOCTOR: GOT IT?
WHERE WAS HE, WHAT WAS HE DOING?

17:53.637 --> 17:55.204
-HE WAS IN THE OCEAN, SWIMMING.

17:55.335 --> 17:57.076
HE COULDN'T BREATHE,
AND HORRIBLE STOMACH CRAMPS

17:57.206 --> 17:58.512
-BLURRY, MY EYES ARE BLURRY,
I CAN'T SEE ANYTHING. [GROAN]

17:59.034 --> 18:01.645
-DOCTOR: PEOPLE, LET'S MOVE.
-ATTENDANT: READY?

18:01.776 --> 18:03.604
-DOCTOR: LET'S GO, LET'S GO.

18:03.734 --> 18:05.214
OKAY, ON MY COUNT.

18:05.345 --> 18:08.174
ONE, TWO, AND THREE.

18:08.304 --> 18:11.133
OKAY, I WANT HIS SKIN
WASHED, THOROUGHLY CHECKED,

18:11.264 --> 18:12.700
FLUSH THE STOMACH
WITH AN NG TUBE,

18:12.830 --> 18:14.963
PREPARE AN ATROPINE
INJECTION RIGHT AWAY.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.051
EXCUSE US.

18:17.748 --> 18:19.315
-WHAT'S WRONG WITH HIM?

18:19.446 --> 18:20.969
-I'M NOT SURE, BUT HE'S
ACTING LIKE HE'S BEEN POISONED.

18:21.622 --> 18:23.885
READY A CARDIAC SUPPORT IN
CASE OF PULMONARY EDEMA.

18:27.280 --> 18:28.846
-FORGET IT, MAN, LOOK
WHAT HAPPENED TO JADE.

18:28.977 --> 18:30.892
-SHE'S A PRO, SHE'LL BE FINE.

18:31.022 --> 18:34.113
-I HAVE A HEADACHE,
ERNIE, IT REALLY HURTS.

18:34.243 --> 18:36.463
I'M NOT GOING IN
THAT WATER AGAIN.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.030
-WHAT'S THE MATTER HERE,
YOU GUYS RUN OUT OF FILM?

18:39.161 --> 18:41.468
-LOOK, THIS IS NONE OF YOUR
BUSINESS, BABE, STAY OUT OF IT.

18:41.598 --> 18:43.470
-MY STOMACH,
IT'S DOING FLIP-FLOPS.

18:43.600 --> 18:44.949
-COME ON, GUYS.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.212
IF YOU WANT A PAYCHECK,
GET BACK TO WORK.

18:46.342 --> 18:47.735
-HEY, WORK IS COOL, ERNIE,

18:47.865 --> 18:48.866
BUT LET'S SLIDE IT DOWN
THE BEACH A LITTLE,

18:48.997 --> 18:50.172
GET AWAY FROM THIS POLLUTION.

18:50.303 --> 18:51.695
COME ON, MAN,
IT'S NOT WORTH IT.

18:51.826 --> 18:53.088
-I'M SICK.

18:53.219 --> 18:54.307
I'M REAL SICK,
-CAROLINE: ALL RIGHT,

18:54.437 --> 18:55.656
LET'S GO.
-I GOT TO GO HOME.

18:55.786 --> 18:56.483
-CAROLINE: WE'VE
HAD ENOUGH, COME ON.

18:57.919 --> 18:59.573
-LOOK, BABIES, COME ON.

18:59.703 --> 19:01.618
I DON'T WANT ANY HASSLE
FROM YOU ANY MORE.

19:01.749 --> 19:02.750
-THAT GIRL IS SICK,
ALL RIGHT?

19:02.880 --> 19:04.186
IT'S PROBABLY FROM THE WATER.

19:04.317 --> 19:05.927
I DON'T WANT ANYONE
ELSE GETTING SICK.

19:06.057 --> 19:07.407
-SHE MAKES SENSE, I'D
LISTEN TO HER IF I WERE YOU.

19:07.537 --> 19:08.712
-WELL, YOU'RE NOT.

19:08.843 --> 19:10.453
I'M A PRO, I KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING.

19:10.584 --> 19:11.846
-YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE
MUCH OF A PRO TO ME.

19:11.976 --> 19:13.326
-OH, YEAH?

19:13.456 --> 19:15.154
WELL, YOU HAVEN'T
SEEN ANY OF MY WORK.

19:15.284 --> 19:17.112
-IF YOU WORKED FOR ME I'D
FIRE YOU RIGHT ON THE SPOT.

19:17.243 --> 19:19.245
-SO WHAT ABOUT THE
REST OF YOU, HUH?

19:19.375 --> 19:21.029
WHAT ARE YOU, GOING
TO GET SICK OR QUIT?

19:25.816 --> 19:28.036
-SHOOT. THAT'S IT.

19:28.167 --> 19:31.126
I'M GOING TO CALL MY LAWYER.
I'M GOING TO SUE BOTH OF YOU.

19:31.692 --> 19:34.303
JADE, WAIT FOR ME.

19:36.871 --> 19:37.741
-C.J.: WHAT'S
WRONG WITH MITCH?

19:37.872 --> 19:39.439
-WE'RE NOT SURE YET.

19:39.569 --> 19:41.267
THE BLURRY VISION, THE SHORTNESS
OF BREATH, THE SEIZURES,

19:41.397 --> 19:43.269
THEY'RE ALL CONSISTENT
WITH POISONING.

19:43.399 --> 19:44.705
-HOW COULD HE GET POISONED?

19:44.835 --> 19:45.967
-WE'RE NOT SURE
OF THAT, EITHER.

19:46.097 --> 19:47.534
WE'RE PUTTING TOGETHER PIECES.

19:47.664 --> 19:50.754
-IF IT IS POISONING,
WHAT CAN YOU DO FOR HIM?

19:50.885 --> 19:52.147
-WELL, WHAT WE'VE
DONE FOR HIM SO FAR

19:52.278 --> 19:53.757
IS JUST A STOP-GAP TREATMENT.

19:53.888 --> 19:55.585
WE WON'T KNOW THE BEST
WAY TO TREAT HIM UNTIL

19:55.716 --> 19:57.979
WE CAN DETERMINE WHAT POISON
HE CAME INTO CONTACT WITH.

19:58.109 --> 19:59.285
-THE RAIN OVER
THE WEEKEND BROUGHT

19:59.415 --> 20:00.764
A LOT OF RUNOFF
INTO THE OCEAN.

20:00.895 --> 20:02.549
I KNOW THE BAY IS
TESTING UNSAFE.

20:02.679 --> 20:03.898
COULD THAT BE THE PROBLEM?

20:04.028 --> 20:05.769
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

20:05.900 --> 20:07.597
YOU SAID HE WAS SWIMMING FAR
OUT AT SEA WHEN HE GOT SICK?

20:07.728 --> 20:09.512
-YEAH.

20:09.643 --> 20:10.992
-NO, ANY BAD WATER WOULD HAVE
BEEN DILUTED THAT FAR OUT.

20:11.122 --> 20:12.820
-IS HE GOING TO BE OKAY?

20:13.647 --> 20:15.170
-WELL, I'LL BE HONEST.

20:15.301 --> 20:17.303
THE NEXT 24 HOURS ARE CRITICAL.

20:17.433 --> 20:18.695
WE'LL DO EVERYTHING WE CAN,

20:18.826 --> 20:20.393
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO
FIND OUT EXACTLY

20:20.523 --> 20:22.482
WHAT POISON HE CAME
INTO CONTACT WITH.

20:24.005 --> 20:25.093
-THANKS.

20:29.793 --> 20:32.709
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

20:40.108 --> 20:41.414
-CODY: WELL,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

20:41.544 --> 20:43.720
-I DON'T KNOW,
IT'S HARD TO TELL.

20:43.851 --> 20:45.505
I MEAN, WE WERE HELPING
MITCH TRAIN FOR THE IRONMAN,

20:45.635 --> 20:46.897
NOT KEEP AN EYE OUT FOR POISON.

20:47.550 --> 20:50.336
THIS IS PRETTY MUCH
OUR COURSE, BUT...

20:50.466 --> 20:52.468
-BUT THE SWIM COVERED
TWO AND A HALF MILES.

20:52.599 --> 20:55.471
-NEELY: YEAH.
-WELL, LET'S GET STARTED.

20:55.602 --> 20:56.516
-LET'S GO.

21:02.913 --> 21:07.353
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:15.508 --> 22:16.465
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

22:20.861 --> 22:21.731
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

22:25.039 --> 22:26.214
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

22:26.345 --> 22:28.085
-NOTHING
IN THE HAZMAT CHARTS.

22:28.216 --> 22:30.131
I'VE CHECKED EVERY INDUSTRIAL
DESIGNER IN THE PHONE BOOK,

22:30.261 --> 22:32.742
EVERY ADVERTISING
BUSINESS ART DEPARTMENT.

22:32.873 --> 22:34.222
NOBODY RECOGNIZES IT.

22:34.744 --> 22:35.919
NADA, ZIP, ZILCH.

22:36.050 --> 22:37.268
-I KNOW.

22:37.399 --> 22:38.661
I'VE CHECKED EVERY
TATTOO PARLOR,

22:38.792 --> 22:39.967
I JUST THAT THEY
WOULD KNOW 'CAUSE

22:40.097 --> 22:40.533
THEY ALWAYS KNOW
EVERYTHING THAT...

22:42.448 --> 22:43.927
I, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M THINKING.

22:47.191 --> 22:48.149
-WHAT?

22:48.279 --> 22:49.455
-WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.

22:49.977 --> 22:54.808
-I AM SO GOOD.
-WHY ARE YOU "SO GOOD"?

22:54.938 --> 22:56.113
-BECAUSE I FIGURED
OUT THAT THIS LOGO

22:56.244 --> 22:57.724
IS REGISTERED TO
STARGER PRODUCE,

22:57.854 --> 22:59.029
IT'S A DISTRIBUTING
COMPANY DOWN ON THE WHARF.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.076
-THAT'S IT.
-HOW'D YOU TRACK IT DOWN?

23:02.206 --> 23:03.425
-I WENT TO THE
COUNTY COURTHOUSE.

23:03.556 --> 23:05.122
I FIGURED THAT
EVERY BUSINESS WOULD

23:05.253 --> 23:06.428
WANT TO REGISTER
THEIR TRADEMARK,

23:06.559 --> 23:08.038
YOU KNOW,
COPYRIGHT THEIR LOGO.

23:08.169 --> 23:09.605
-YOU ARE GOOD.
LET'S GO.

23:33.934 --> 23:35.544
-YEAH, THAT'S OUR
LOGO, WHAT ABOUT IT?

23:35.675 --> 23:37.372
-WELL, WE FOUND A COUPLE
OF METAL STORAGE DRUMS

23:37.503 --> 23:40.114
WITH YOUR LOGO ON THEM AT
THE BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN.

23:40.244 --> 23:41.637
-STORAGE DRUMS.

23:41.768 --> 23:43.639
LOOK, WE DISTRIBUTE
VEGETABLES.

23:43.770 --> 23:46.381
WE PACK IN WOODEN
CRATES, NOT METAL DRUMS.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.252
-WELL, A GOOD FRIEND OF
OURS SWAM OVER THOSE DRUMS

23:48.383 --> 23:49.297
AND HE'S VERY SICK NOW.

23:49.428 --> 23:50.777
NOW HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

23:50.907 --> 23:52.343
-WE THINK THAT HE
MIGHT HAVE BEEN POISONED

23:52.474 --> 23:54.128
BY WHATEVER COULD HAVE
BEEN IN THOSE DRUMS.

23:54.258 --> 23:56.260
-OH, LOOK, I MEAN, EVEN IF
WE DID PACK IN METAL DRUMS,

23:56.391 --> 23:57.653
WHICH WE DON'T,

23:58.349 --> 24:02.049
THEY WOULD BE FULL OF BRUSSELS
SPROUTS, LETTUCE, NOT POISON.

24:02.179 --> 24:03.746
-WELL, THEN HOW'D YOUR
LOGO GET ON THOSE DRUMS?

24:03.877 --> 24:05.966
-I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE YOU
GUYS MADE A MISTAKE, HUH?

24:06.096 --> 24:09.273
-MR. SCANLON, IF IT WAS POISON,
WE NEED TO FIND OUT FAST.

24:09.404 --> 24:10.797
-OUR FRIEND COULD DIE.

24:10.927 --> 24:14.453
-LOOK, I TOLD YOU
GUYS, VEGETABLES, HUH?

24:15.932 --> 24:16.933
YOU SEE?

24:17.456 --> 24:18.848
THESE ARE GOOD FOR YOU.

24:18.979 --> 24:20.110
HUH?

24:21.764 --> 24:23.592
NOW, I GOT A LOT OF
WORK TO GET DONE.

24:24.506 --> 24:25.812
WHAT I TOLD YOU
IS ALL THAT I KNOW

24:25.942 --> 24:27.291
AND IT'S NOT GOING
TO CHANGE,

24:27.422 --> 24:28.292
SO I'LL SEE YOU GUYS
LATER, ALL RIGHT?

24:30.512 --> 24:31.644
-I HATE BROCCOLI.

24:36.039 --> 24:39.565
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

24:47.137 --> 24:48.312
-THEY BUY IT?

24:49.966 --> 24:50.967
-I'M NOT SURE.

24:52.795 --> 24:53.753
I THINK SO.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.407
-WHAT IF THEY DIDN'T?

24:58.018 --> 24:59.367
-CALL BOGGS.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.369
TELL HIM HE'S GOT
A PICK-UP AND DELIVERY.

25:02.588 --> 25:04.590
-THAT FRIEND OF THEIRS,
HE SOUNDS PRETTY BAD OFF.

25:04.720 --> 25:06.679
MAYBE WE JUST, JUST OUGHT
TO TELL THEM, YOU KNOW?

25:06.809 --> 25:09.159
-AND GET BUSTED
FOR ILLEGAL DUMPING?

25:09.290 --> 25:10.247
I DON'T THINK SO.

25:10.378 --> 25:11.988
-A FINE IS ONE THING,

25:12.119 --> 25:13.903
BUT IF THAT GUY DIES THAT'S
ACCOMPLICE TO MURDER.

25:14.034 --> 25:15.731
-CALL BOGGS.

25:15.862 --> 25:17.516
AND THIS ALL GOES AWAY.

25:19.387 --> 25:23.173
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

26:07.087 --> 26:08.262
-LOOKING FOR SOMETHING?

26:08.784 --> 26:10.786
-UM, I, MY QUARTER.

26:10.917 --> 26:12.005
I DROPPED IT.

26:12.135 --> 26:14.094
-PRETTY IMPORTANT QUARTER.

26:14.224 --> 26:15.791
-YEAH, YOU KNOW,
WHEN YOU REALLY HAVE
TO MAKE A PHONE CALL,

26:15.922 --> 26:17.227
AND IT'S YOUR LAST ONE 'CAUSE
YOUR FRIENDS LEFT YOU--

26:17.358 --> 26:18.620
-WHAT ARE YOU UP TO, LADY?
-WHAT ARE YOU--

26:18.751 --> 26:19.447
LET GO OF ME!
-CODY: THERE YOU ARE.

26:20.709 --> 26:23.016
-HEY, I, I THOUGHT
YOU GUYS DITCHED ME.

26:23.146 --> 26:24.495
-CODY: WE DIDN'T DITCH YOU.

26:25.453 --> 26:26.628
-LOOKS LIKE YOU DITCHED US.

26:26.759 --> 26:28.238
-NO, I-I WOULDN'T DO THAT.

26:29.196 --> 26:30.676
-I SHOULD BUST
ALL THREE OF YOU.

26:30.806 --> 26:33.417
-FOR WHAT. GRAND
THEFT BROCCOLI?

26:39.206 --> 26:41.295
[MONITOR BEEPING]

26:41.425 --> 26:43.558
[MONITOR FLATLINE TONE]

26:44.211 --> 26:45.516
-PADDLES, STAT.

26:49.433 --> 26:50.304
CHARGING.
-NURSE: READY.

26:50.434 --> 26:51.871
-CLEAR.
-NURSE: CLEAR.

26:53.350 --> 26:55.265
[FLAT TONE]

26:55.962 --> 26:57.180
-CLEAR.

27:08.322 --> 27:09.628
HE'S IN A COMA.

27:10.411 --> 27:13.414
[MONITOR BEEPING]

27:16.939 --> 27:19.550
I WANT HALF HOUR UPDATES
ON HIS EEG RESULTS.

27:19.681 --> 27:20.726
-NURSE: YES, DOCTOR.

27:25.774 --> 27:27.123
[CAR HORN HONKS]

27:42.791 --> 27:43.966
-SIR, EXCUSE ME.

27:44.097 --> 27:45.185
I'M AFRAID
THE BEACH IS CLOSED.

27:45.315 --> 27:47.274
-WHAT?
YOU CAN'T CLOSE A BEACH.

27:47.404 --> 27:48.884
-YEAH, I CAN.

27:49.015 --> 27:51.060
THE TOXIC LEVEL IN THE
WATER GRADES OUT AS AN F.

27:51.191 --> 27:52.496
-HEY, I'M A TAXPAYER.

27:52.627 --> 27:55.195
I PAY GOOD MONEY
TO KEEP THE BEACH OPEN.

27:55.325 --> 27:57.153
WHY CAN'T YOU GUYS PUT
SOMETHING IN THE WATER?

27:57.284 --> 27:58.502
-WELL, SOMEBODY
ALREADY DID THAT.

27:58.633 --> 28:00.069
THAT'S WHY
THE WATER'S POLLUTED.

28:00.983 --> 28:02.202
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

28:02.332 --> 28:03.594
COME ON, LET'S GO.

28:07.729 --> 28:08.774
STUPID.

28:12.473 --> 28:14.693
-YOU KNOW, YOU OUGHT
TO CHECK YOUR OIL, TOO.

28:14.823 --> 28:16.782
-I JUST CHANGED IT, OKAY?

28:20.611 --> 28:21.656
-JERK.

28:28.750 --> 28:30.709
[SERENE MUSIC]

28:41.371 --> 28:43.373
-EXCUSE ME, THE WATER'S BAD.

28:43.504 --> 28:44.810
THERE'S NO SURFING
TODAY, I'M AFRAID.

28:44.940 --> 28:46.855
-I WASN'T GOING TO SURF.

28:46.986 --> 28:49.205
I WAS GOING TO SWIM
WITH THE DOLPHINS.

28:49.336 --> 28:50.946
-WITH THE DOLPHINS?

28:51.077 --> 28:52.295
REALLY?

28:52.426 --> 28:54.254
-YEAH, THEY LOVE
TO SWIM WITH HUMANS.

28:54.384 --> 28:56.691
-HOW DO YOU
AND THE DOLPHINS HOOK UP?

28:56.822 --> 28:59.085
-YOU JUST LET THEM KNOW
YOU WANT TO SWIM WITH THEM.

28:59.781 --> 29:01.870
IT'S THIS ENERGY
YOU SHARE WITH THEM.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.046
IT'S NOT FAIR.

29:04.699 --> 29:06.440
THEY DON'T TRASH
OUR NEIGHBORHOOD.

29:13.012 --> 29:14.709
-NEELY, WAIT UP, HEY.

29:14.840 --> 29:16.145
WHAT'S THE LATEST ON MITCH?

29:16.276 --> 29:17.756
-NOT GOOD.

29:17.886 --> 29:19.322
I'M GOING TO THE HOSPITAL NOW.
-YOU KNOW WHAT?

29:19.453 --> 29:20.846
GIVE ME FIVE MINUTES,
I WANT TO GO WITH YOU.

29:20.976 --> 29:22.238
-OKAY, I'LL BE WAITING
FOR YOU OUT FRONT.

29:22.848 --> 29:23.936
-HEY, DONNA, WAIT UP.

29:25.285 --> 29:28.201
-OH, HI, YOU'RE THE GUY FROM
INSIDE SPORTS. JERRY, RIGHT?

29:28.331 --> 29:29.811
-GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.
-YEAH, HOW'RE YOU DOING?

29:29.942 --> 29:31.247
-GOOD. YOU KNOW, WHAT
HAPPENED ON THE BEACH

29:31.378 --> 29:32.727
EARLIER TODAY GOT
ME THINKING AND I'VE GOT

29:32.858 --> 29:34.555
A COUPLE OF IDEAS
I'D LIKE TO RUN BY YOU.

29:35.077 --> 29:37.166
THAT PHOTOGRAPHER,
HE WAS A REAL KNUCKLEHEAD,

29:37.297 --> 29:38.602
AND HE WAS WRONG ABOUT
ALL KINDS OF THINGS,

29:38.733 --> 29:39.865
BUT HE WAS RIGHT
ABOUT ONE THING.

29:39.995 --> 29:41.388
YOU ARE COVER GIRL MATERIAL.

29:41.518 --> 29:43.042
-OH, YEAH, NO,
I'M NOT INTERESTED.

29:43.172 --> 29:44.478
-AND, YOU KNOW,
WE DO THIS INSIDE SPORTS

29:44.608 --> 29:46.088
SWIMSUIT ISSUE EVERY YEAR;

29:46.219 --> 29:47.960
WE'D LOVE TO HAVE
YOU ON THE COVER.

29:48.090 --> 29:49.309
-WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT, I'VE
GOT A FRIEND IN THE HOSPITAL,

29:49.439 --> 29:50.614
I'M ON MY WAY TO SEE.

29:50.745 --> 29:52.181
-YEAH, I HEARD,
THAT'S THE POINT.

29:52.312 --> 29:53.966
HE GOT POISONED WHILE
SWIMMING IN THE OCEAN.

29:54.096 --> 29:56.185
-EXACTLY, SO IF YOU COULD
EXCUSE ME, I'VE GOT TO GO.

29:56.316 --> 29:57.926
-BUT WAIT,
HEAR MY SECOND IDEA.

29:58.057 --> 29:59.972
I'LL WRITE AN ARTICLE
ABOUT ECOLOGY.

30:00.102 --> 30:01.712
I'LL TALK ABOUT HOW
TO CLEAN UP THE OCEAN,

30:01.843 --> 30:03.671
HOW TO MAKE THE WATER
A BETTER PLACE TO BE.

30:04.280 --> 30:06.848
IT'S YOUR OFFICE,
IT'S WHERE MY READERS SWIM.

30:06.979 --> 30:09.198
-I DON'T KNOW.
-WE'RE GOING TO THE BAHAMAS.

30:09.329 --> 30:10.765
WE'RE GOING TO STAY
ON PARADISE ISLAND

30:10.896 --> 30:12.158
AT THE ATLANTIS HOTEL.

30:12.767 --> 30:15.161
COME ON, TOGETHER
WE CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

30:16.989 --> 30:19.600
[SERENE MUSIC]

30:53.155 --> 30:54.809
-WELL, I DON'T SEE
ANYBODY ELSE AROUND.

30:54.940 --> 30:56.724
-LET'S HOPE NOBODY SEES US.

31:01.076 --> 31:03.209
-ISN'T THIS BREAKING
AND ENTERING?

31:03.949 --> 31:05.428
-SO FAR IT'S JUST ENTERING.

31:06.255 --> 31:07.691
JUST DON'T BREAK ANYTHING.

31:09.432 --> 31:12.000
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

31:29.800 --> 31:31.367
-THIS IS IT, YOU GUYS,
I WAS RIGHT, COME HERE.

31:34.631 --> 31:36.372
-THAT'S IT, THAT'S THE LOGO.

31:36.503 --> 31:38.026
-WE GOT TO FIND OUT WHAT KIND
OF STUFF'S IN THESE BAD BOYS

31:38.157 --> 31:39.549
AND GIVE IT
TO MITCH'S DOCTORS.

31:40.289 --> 31:42.770
-UH-OH, THEY'RE HERE.

31:49.559 --> 31:50.430
-LET'S GO.

31:56.088 --> 31:57.567
-WE GOT THREE
TO PICK UP HERE,

31:57.698 --> 31:58.960
THEN WE SWING AROUND
TO CUTTER'S WAREHOUSE,

31:59.091 --> 32:00.483
PICK UP ANOTHER SIX.

32:00.614 --> 32:02.572
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
THE CRANE IN PLACE.

32:02.703 --> 32:04.400
I WANT TO GET THESE
DRUMS MOVED NOW.

32:14.889 --> 32:15.890
-LET'S GET THIS DONE.

32:16.021 --> 32:17.544
I WANT
TO GET HOME, ALL RIGHT?

32:17.674 --> 32:19.024
THE FIGHT'S ON PAY-PER-VIEW,

32:19.154 --> 32:20.329
I DON'T WANT TO
JUST THROW AWAY 40 BUCKS.

32:20.460 --> 32:22.114
LET'S GO, COME ON, MOVE!

32:22.636 --> 32:25.204
-MAN: OKAY, JUST A SECOND.

32:27.989 --> 32:28.947
